r $\\rho_{\\omega }$\nbehaves monotonically with respect to $\\omega $. We show, using again a\ncomputer-aided proof, that this is not the case when $\\epsilon \\geq 1$ and the\nmap is not a diffeomorphism.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Apr 2019 09:52:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 May 2019 18:34:56 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Jan 2020 20:07:36 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 24 Jan 2020 16:43:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-27"}
